I’m been to Nandos multiple times. I’ve had food delivered from this location before, but Dec 29th was my first time ever eating in the location, and I must say, it was certainly a delight. I bought 8 members of my family with. My grandfather, who is an extremely picky eater, won’t eat ethnic food, and generally does not like much seasoning, cleaned his plate of grilled chicken. He ordered the plainish and said it certainly wasn’t plain, but that he enjoyed the flavors. He did say the fries were a little bit too seasoned for him, but he still ate most of them. I generally order the Medium heat and a half chicken. I always get peri-peri fries, which are quite good, and garlic bread, which is truly the best garlic bread I’ve ever had. I just found out about Nandos in August, and have probably had it at least 7 or 8 times since. And other than one time when my fries were forgotten, I’ve had nothing but good experiences. If you are at union station, you can either walk or take the street tram there. It’s definitely a must do if you are on or around H street. And this location as so much character. The building, the decorations, the friendly and accommodating staff. They pushed a table together for us immediately as we walked in the door. They also sell their sauces too. I got some for Christmas. And they are one of the few places I can get Dole whip. The Pineapple lemonade is also delicious, and though I haven’t had a sangria there before, I’m sure I will at some point, and it will probably been delicious as well. Keep up the good work!

At first, I wasn't a fan of Nando's PERi-PERi since I don't love meat on the bone (no wings for me!). However, now that I know they are much more than chicken on the bone, I am a fan. Here's why:  1) History: They are a South African brand gone global. They are all over Europe and DC is one of two markets in the USA (the other is Chicago). They support 1,200 South African farmers who grow the special pepper in everything they cook. In addition, they have the largest collection of contemporary South African art.  2) Food: For the price, it's good! They have all chicken products and their boneless chicken breast sandwiches are always great especially the one on garlic bread and coleslaw. They also have a secret hack menu that includes spicy fries and cheesy mashed potatoes. Also, their avocado toast is amazing.  3) Space: Each restaurant is spacious and beautifully designed. This location has two floors and you can always find a seat. It's the largest location in the DC.
